# Vercel Plugin Ā· AI coding agent resource

The **Vercel Plugin** (`vercel/vercel-plugin`) gives Cursor and other supported
agents Vercel-specific context: an ecosystem graph, skills, specialist agents,
and slash commands. It is **agent tooling ā€” not a credential store**. It fits the
BRMSTE human-open lane: free, no tokens in chat, carbon justice only.

Docs: <https://vercel.com/docs/agent-resources/vercel-plugin> Ā· Source: <https://github.com/vercel/vercel-plugin>

## Install (operator, outside chat)

```bash
npx plugins add vercel/vercel-plugin
```

- Prerequisites: a supported tool (Cursor, Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, Grok Build, GitHub Copilot), **Node.js 18+**, and **Bun**.
- Scope flag: `-s user|project|local` (default `user`); target flag: `-t cursor|claude-code|codex`; `-y` to skip prompts; `--debug` for verbose output.
- Inspect before install: `npx plugins discover vercel/vercel-plugin` Ā· list targets: `npx plugins targets`.

## Cloud agents (this repo)

Cursor **cloud agents already receive the plugin** through the managed environment
(`~/.cursor/plugins/cache/.cloud-plugin-manifest.json`, plugin id `649`). No
per-repo install step is required for cloud agents ā€” the skills, the three
specialist agents, and the slash commands are provisioned automatically.

## What it provides

| Component | Notes |
|-----------|-------|
| Ecosystem graph | Relational map of every Vercel product, library, CLI, API with decision matrices |
| 28 skills | e.g. `nextjs`, `ai-sdk`, `ai-gateway`, `vercel-cli`, `vercel-functions`, `vercel-storage`, `deployments-cicd`, `env-vars`, `verification` |
| 3 specialist agents | `deployment-expert`, `performance-optimizer`, `ai-architect` |
| 5 slash commands | `/vercel-plugin:bootstrap`, `:deploy`, `:env`, `:status`, `:marketplace` |

Invoke directly, e.g. `/vercel-plugin:nextjs`, `/vercel-plugin:deploy prod`.
Session-start context auto-injects **only** in empty directories and detected
Vercel/Next.js projects; skills otherwise load on demand.

## MCP-strict alignment Ā· never ask for tokens

- The plugin ships an optional Vercel MCP wiring (`.mcp.json`). Connect it the
  BRMSTE way: **Cursor ā†’ Settings ā†’ Tools & MCP ā†’ Connect**. **Never** paste a
  Vercel token, `VERCEL_TOKEN`, or deploy key into chat. See
  [`mcp-strict-only.mdc`](mcp-strict-only.mdc).
- Vercel deploys on the open lane stay token-free in conversation: operator CI
  (GitHub Actions) or Cursor-connected MCP, not chat-pasted secrets.

## Telemetry Ā· privacy default

Disable the plugin's once-per-day active-ping in shells that launch the agent:

```bash
export VERCEL_PLUGIN_TELEMETRY=off
```

Prompt text and tool-call telemetry are not collected; `off` also drops the daily
`dau:active_today` event.

## Debug

```bash
export VERCEL_PLUGIN_LOG_LEVEL=debug   # off | summary | debug | trace
npx vercel-plugin doctor               # manifest parity, hook timeout, dedup, skill map
```

